- ts: 2026-04-28T00:00:00Z
  event: clarify_critic
  feature: extract-backlog-pick-ready-set-into-bin-backlog-ready
  findings:
    - "The High Intent rating ignores an internal naming contradiction: title says bin/backlog-ready but Scope says bin/cortex-backlog-ready; the assessment silently picks the Scope name using outside repo convention rather than acknowledging the source disagrees with itself."
    - "The High Intent rating treats 'priority-grouped ready items as JSON' as unambiguous, but the source does not specify the JSON shape, the precise filter predicate, or whether priority groups are ordered — load-bearing contract surface for a script that mediates between SKILL.md and the agent."
    - "The High Scope boundedness rating quotes the in-scope/out-of-scope bullets verbatim and treats their existence as sufficient; the bullets enumerate artifacts but not behavioral boundaries (flags, filter predicate, empty-set handling, stale-index handling), and the relationship to the sibling /backlog ready subcommand is unaddressed."
    - "The Requirements alignment rating cites 'SKILL.md-to-bin parity enforcement' from project.md and DR-2 from research without quoting either; alignment is asserted rather than demonstrated."
    - "The criticality rating of medium rests on a graceful-degradation fallback ('agent can fall back to inline reads') that the ticket does not authorize — Scope says 'Update SKILL.md pick flow to invoke the script,' which replaces inline reads, so a broken script breaks /backlog pick outright."
    - "The complexity rating of simple is asserted without naming the existing pattern that justifies 'follows existing pattern' or counting files against the 1-3 threshold."
  dispositions:
    apply: 3
    dismiss: 3
    ask: 1
  applied_fixes:
    - "Added Research open question covering JSON output schema, precise filter predicate, and group ordering (Finding 2)."
    - "Quoted project.md's SKILL.md-to-bin parity constraint verbatim in the Requirements alignment note (Finding 4)."
    - "Revised criticality from medium to high — the ticket replaces the inline reads, so a broken script breaks /backlog pick. Skill-layer changes default to high per the rubric (Finding 5)."
    - "Downgraded Scope boundedness from High to Low and added research open questions for behavioral details (Finding 3, partial Apply portion)."
  dismissals:
    - finding_index: 0
      rationale: "The Scope section explicitly specifies bin/cortex-backlog-ready, which is the controlling text; the title is a colloquial reference. No genuine ambiguity in artifact name."
    - finding_index: 2
      rationale: "Partial Apply: behavioral details are routed to research as open questions, and the /backlog ready overlap is the lone consequential question forwarded to the user. Remaining boundedness gap is closed by the user-facing Ask, not by re-rating."
    - finding_index: 5
      rationale: "The existing pattern is bin/cortex-generate-backlog-index — same family (read backlog/index.json, emit derived view). Counting against simple threshold: new bin script + SKILL.md edit + plugin mirror via just build-plugin = 1-3 files in scope. Simple stands."
  status: ok
